19/03/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- BiH Prime Minister Adnan Terzic and new Defence Minister Nikola Radovanovic met with representatives of the EU and NATO Thursday (18 March) to discuss the future transfer of military command in BiH from NATO to the EU.
NATO officials again gave assurances that the Alliance would stay in BiH even after SFOR hands over its mandate to an EU force.
In other news, the chairman of the Republika Srpska Helsinki Board for Human Rights, Branko Todorovic, indicated on Thursday that he does not believe BiH prosecutors are ready to tackle war crimes cases.
He cited technical and administrative problems.
(OHR Sources, Oslobodjenje, Nezavisne novine - 19/03/04)
